</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-415">The velocity between 1 and 2 s is constant and as such acceleration is zero. The resulting displacement – time curve for this time interval is a straight line having slope equal to that of the magnitude of velocity. 
</para>
<para id="element-416">
The displacement at the end of 2 s is 5 + 10 = 15 m
</para>
<para id="element-417">Now, the displacement between times 2 and 4 s is :
</para>
<para id="element-418">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mo> Δ </m:mo>
<m:mi> x </m:mi>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mfrac>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
</m:mfrac>
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:mo> x </m:mo> 
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:mo> ( </m:mo> 
<m:mn> 20 </m:mn>
<m:mo> + </m:mo> 
