<para id="element-5055a">
<exercise id="exercise-5055a">
<problem id="idp981184">
<para id="element-79"> The motion of a body in one dimension is given by the equation dv(t)/dt = 6.0 -3 v (t), where v(t) is the velocity in m/s and “t” in seconds. If the body was at rest at t = 0, then find the magnitude of the initial acceleration and also find the velocity, when the acceleration is half the initial value.
</para>

</problem>

<solution id="idp283616">
<para id="element-80">  We have to find the acceleration at t = 0 from the equation given as :
</para>
<para id="element-85">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mfrac>
<m:mrow>
